text: Pour is a cloudy yellow with a large white head. Aroma is a nice pils bready malt and a big lemony hop. Flavor is a little bit thinner than the aroma let on. You still get a decent bready malt with the hops its just a little watery. I dont think being brewed in the California Common style added anything to the beer. It is a solid pils though.

Light in body, high on the hops. Not my favourite kind of beer; but it's decent for the style. Fall brewing sd

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Pours a golden yellow color with a slight sweet aroma. Taste is light, easy drinking, with a minor malt sweetness. Nicely made beer for the style just not complex.
On tap at the brewery. Pours a hazy yellow gold with small frothy white head that lasts. The aroma is grass and yeast. Medium body, grass, lemon zest, yeast, light finish, very nice.
Tap. Pours clear yellow/gold. Aroma and flavor are pale malt, light toast, floral notes, faint citrus, and a crisp, dry finish.

UPDATED: JAN 5, 2017 Draft at Plan 9. Pours clear bright gold with a fizzy white head. Tastes like corn, doughy malt, dry straw, and grass. Light body and low carbonation. Smells like corn doughy malt, dry straw, and grass.

Draught at Plan 9. Pours clear gold with a small, frothy white head, medium retention with good lacing. Aroma is heavy Pils malt, corny notes and medium woody hops. Flavor is moderate corny Pils malt, medium woody hops and bitterness with a dry finish. Light body and moderate carbonation.
Draft. Pours gold with a white head. Grainy, almost rustic base, with faint honey sweetness, low bitterness, and mild grassy notes. Solid; very drinkable.

Sampled at GABF 2025. In the sample glass gold with a white head. Nose of grassy hop;s and caramel malts. Medium body. Smooth mouthfeel. Flavor is citrus and grassy hops, and there is a light bitter finish. Easy drinking.

Taster. Pale gold with white head. Mild hop aroma, sweet malts... Crisp and clean... Very nice.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Draught @ Cicos, San Diego. Aroma has grainy malt, butter and some fruitiness. Flavour has buttery malt, grain, some cereal and mild fruitiness. Also grass. Somewhat refreshing.

Draught @ Ciros, San Diego, CA. Pours yellowish golden with a smooth foamy head. Aroma of crisp malts, some grass, hay and sweetish notes. Taste is sweetish, malty and slightly grassy with some hints of hay and citrus. Finish is smooth, sweetish and slightly malty with hints of grass. Okay.

Lightly hazy gold with a stark white head. Powerful lemon and grass aroma. Medium, crisp, clean body. Flavor is lemon, grass, medium citrus. Really nice summer drinker. Clean and refreshing and awesome.

On tap at the brewery. It pours a clear yellow color with a white head. The aroma is grainy with light floral/earthy noble hops. The flavor is grassy and earthy with clean pale maltiness. Good medium floral earthy bitterness. Very nice and well balanced.

[ Tap ][ 4oz ][ Fall North Park ][ $2 ][ Tasting Stange ][ 2.27.15 ]
>> Pours clear straw with webby white lacing. Nose is fresh biscuit, honey roll, grassy hops. Taste is pretty much a great intro Pils, good balancing sugar, mild grainy note, rustic, bready, honey rolls. Mildly oily body. Quite good.
Tap at brewery, gold pour, white head, nose is lacking, taste is lemons, light citrus, grassy, okay
Bonne atténuation et bonne mousse, des zestes pulpeux et une buvabilité grandiose. Simple et bien concocté.

On tap @ Fall Brewing. Clear golden pour with a white head. Smells like a typical industrial lager. A lot of cereal grain and corn. A big time Keystone Light smell to it. Reminds me of the fraternity house. Flavor is pretty much like your 14th pale lager of the night. A lot of sweet cereal grains and grain husk. Kind of grassy and lightly bitter but mostly sweet and grainy. Tastes like college.
